org.wattdepot.client.restlet

Class WattDepotClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wattdepot.client.restlet.WattDepotClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WattDepotInterface
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    WattDepotAdminClient

    public class WattDepotClient
extends Object
implements WattDepotInterface
    WattDepotClient - high-level Java implementation that communicates with a WattDepot3 server. It implements the WattDepotInterface that hides the HTTP API.
    Author:
    Cam Moore

    • Constructor Detail

      • WattDepotClient

        public WattDepotClient(String serverUri,
               String username,
               String password)
                throws BadCredentialException
        Creates a new WattDepotClient.
        Parameters:
        serverUri - The URI of the WattDepot server (e.g. "http://server.wattdepot.org/")
        username - The name of the user. The user must be defined in the WattDepot server.
        password - The password for the user.
        Throws:
        BadCredentialException - If the user or password don't match the credentials on the WattDepot server.

      • getValue

        public Double getValue(Depository depository,
              Sensor sensor,
              Date timestamp)
                throws NoMeasurementException
        Specified by:
        getValue in interface WattDepotInterface
        Parameters:
        depository - The Depository storing the measurements.
        sensor - The sensor making the measurements.
        timestamp - The time for the measured value.
        Returns:
        The Value 'measured' at the given time, most likely an interpolated value.
        Throws:
        NoMeasurementException - if there aren't any measurements around the timestamp.

      • getValue

        public Double getValue(Depository depository,
              Sensor sensor,
              Date start,
              Date end)
                throws NoMeasurementException
        Specified by:
        getValue in interface WattDepotInterface
        Parameters:
        depository - The Depository storing the measurements.
        sensor - The sensor making the measurements.
        start - The start of the period.
        end - The end of the period.
        Returns:
        The value measured the difference between the end value and the start value.
        Throws:
        NoMeasurementException - if there are no measurements around the start or end time.

      • getValue

        public Double getValue(Depository depository,
              Sensor sensor,
              Date start,
              Date end,
              Long gapSeconds)
                throws NoMeasurementException,
                       MeasurementGapException
        Specified by:
        getValue in interface WattDepotInterface
        Parameters:
        depository - The Depository storing the measurements.
        sensor - The Sensor making the measurements.
        start - The start of the interval.
        end - The end of the interval
        gapSeconds - The maximum number of seconds that measurements need to be within the start and end.
        Returns:
        The value measured the difference between the end value and the start value.
        Throws:
        NoMeasurementException - if there are no measurements around the start or end time.
        MeasurementGapException - if the measurements around start or end are too far apart.

      • getValue

        public Double getValue(Depository depository,
              Sensor sensor,
              Date timestamp,
              Long gapSeconds)
                throws NoMeasurementException,
                       MeasurementGapException
        Specified by:
        getValue in interface WattDepotInterface
        Parameters:
        depository - The Depository storing the measurements.
        sensor - The Sensor making the measurements.
        timestamp - The time of the value.
        gapSeconds - The maximum number of seconds that measurements need to be within the start and end.
        Returns:
        The Value 'measured' at the given time, most likely an interpolated value.
        Throws:
        NoMeasurementException - If there aren't any measurements around the time.
        MeasurementGapException - if the measurements around timestamp are too far apart.
